 Master Node (SSH Key Setup & Transfer)

    ssh-keygen -t rsa — Generates a public-private SSH key pair (press Enter to accept defaults).

    ssh-copy-id user@192.168.50.64 — Copies the master’s public key to the worker node for password-less login.

    ssh user@192.168.50.64 — Verifies that the master can now SSH into the worker without entering a password.

 Worker Node (SSH Access Configuration)

    sudo apt install openssh-server — Installs the SSH server if not already installed.

    sudo systemctl enable ssh — Enables the SSH service to start on boot.

    sudo systemctl start ssh — Starts the SSH service immediately.

    sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config — Opens the SSH configuration file for editing.

    PasswordAuthentication no — (Edit inside the file) Disables password-based login (optional, for enhanced security).

    PermitRootLogin no — (Edit inside the file) Disallows root login via SSH (recommended).

    sudo systemctl restart ssh — Applies the new SSH configuration by restarting the SSH service.

To Send File:
scp filename username@ip:location to where the file will be sent.
e.g. scp myfile.txt@192.168.50.64:/home/user/


